───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§ 1. DEFINITIONS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

For the purposes of this License, the following definitions apply:

  1.1  "Software" means the NEURO project source code, binaries, assets,
       documentation, algorithms, data structures, system architecture, design
       patterns, and all associated materials published at the official project
       repository or distributed by the NEURO Project Contributors.

  1.2  "Contributor" means any individual or legal entity that has submitted
       code, documentation, or other materials to the NEURO project repository
       and whose contributions have been accepted.

  1.3  "Derivative Work" means any work, whether in source or object form,
       that is based on or derived from the Software, including modifications,
       adaptations, translations, ports, forks, or any work that incorporates
       a substantial portion of the Software's expressive elements.

  1.4  "AI System" means any artificial intelligence, machine learning model,
       large language model (LLM), neural network, autonomous agent, automated
       pipeline, or AI-assisted tool or workflow capable of reading, parsing,
       analyzing, synthesizing, or generating code, documentation, or software
       architecture.

  1.5  "AI-Assisted Reproduction" means any process in which an AI System
       reads, analyzes, summarizes, or otherwise processes the Software or
       any substantial portion thereof, and such process results in — or
       materially contributes to — the creation of a separate codebase,
       product, or system that replicates, mirrors, or substantially recreates
       the functionality, architecture, design decisions, or novel elements of
       the Software.

  1.6  "Structural Cloning" means the creation of a new software project
       whose overall architecture, module organization, algorithmic approach,
       or design philosophy is substantially similar to the Software, regardless
       of whether source code was directly copied, transformed, or regenerated.

  1.7  "Commercial Use" means any use of the Software, or a Derivative Work
       thereof, for direct or indirect financial gain, including but not limited
       to integration into paid products, SaaS offerings, consulting services,
       or internal business tooling.

  1.8  "You" or "Recipient" means any individual, organization, or legal entity
       that accesses, downloads, clones, forks, reads, runs, modifies, or
       distributes the Software in any form.

