§ 2. MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION AND COPYRIGHT PRESERVATION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  2.1  Any redistribution of the Software, whether in source or binary form,
       must include the following attribution in a prominent, user-accessible
       location (such as a README, About page, application splash screen,
       or license documentation):

         Based on NEURO (https://github.com/PanzerPeter/Neuro)
         Copyright (C) 2024–2025 NEURO Project Contributors

  2.2  The following elements must be preserved verbatim and in their entirety
       in all copies, distributions, and Derivative Works:

         (a) All existing copyright notices;
         (b) The Alpha Version Notice (Part I of this License);
         (c) This full License document, including the Supplementary Sections.

  2.3  Attribution must not be formatted or placed in a manner that obscures,
       diminishes, or renders it effectively invisible to end users. Placement
       in minified bundles, compiled binaries without a corresponding readable
       NOTICE file, or deep within undiscoverable configuration files does not
       satisfy this requirement.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§ 3. MANDATORY ALPHA STATUS DISCLOSURE IN ALL DISTRIBUTIONS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  3.1  Any redistribution — whether of the original Software or a Derivative
       Work — must include the Alpha Version Notice (Part I) verbatim.

  3.2  All user-facing materials associated with a redistribution must carry a
       prominent and unambiguous statement that the software is an alpha release
       and may exhibit instability, data loss, or unexpected behavior.

  3.3  You may not present the Software, or any Derivative Work thereof, to
       end users in a manner that implies production-readiness, stability, or
       fitness for mission-critical use, unless you have independently verified
       and documented its suitability for such use and clearly label it as
       a separately maintained fork under a distinct name per § 5.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§ 4. DOCUMENTATION OF MODIFICATIONS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  4.1  If you distribute a modified version of the Software, you must:

         (a) Clearly mark every modified file with a comment or header
             indicating it has been modified, the date of modification,
             and the identity of the modifying party;

         (b) Include a plaintext file named "CHANGES" or "MODIFICATIONS"
             at the root of the distribution, summarizing all material
             changes, including: the nature of each change, the author(s)
             responsible, and the date(s) of modification;

         (c) Not represent or imply that a modified version is the original,
             unmodified NEURO project.

  4.2  The CHANGES file must be updated with each new release or distribution
       of a modified version. Cumulative changelogs that omit intermediate
       changes do not satisfy this requirement.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§ 5. NAMING AND IDENTITY OF DERIVATIVE WORKS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  5.1  Derivative Works must be distributed under a name that is clearly and
       meaningfully distinct from "NEURO" so as not to create confusion
       regarding the origin or official status of the project.

  5.2  You may not use any of the following, or names confusingly similar
       thereto, without explicit prior written consent from the NEURO Project:

         — "NEURO" as a standalone product or project name
         — "Neuro Engine", "NeuroAI", "NeuroPlatform", or any compound
           name where "NEURO" is the dominant identifying element
         — The official NEURO project logotype, icon set, or visual identity

  5.3  You must explicitly state in user-visible documentation that your
       Derivative Work is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or an official
       release of the NEURO Project.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§ 6. SOURCE AVAILABILITY FOR BINARY DISTRIBUTIONS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  6.1  If you distribute the Software or any Derivative Work in compiled,
       binary, or otherwise non-human-readable form, you must comply fully
