         (a) Include a plaintext NOTICE file at the root of the distribution
             containing the URL or mechanism by which complete corresponding
             source code may be obtained;

         (b) Ensure that source availability is maintained for no less than
             three (3) years from the date of the binary distribution.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
§ 7. RESTRICTIONS ON AI-ASSISTED REPRODUCTION AND STRUCTURAL CLONING
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This section addresses a class of intellectual property harm not contemplated
by the GPL v3.0: the use of AI Systems to analyze open-source projects and
produce functional replicas or near-equivalent systems without authorization.

  7.1  PROHIBITION ON AI-ASSISTED REPRODUCTION

       You may not, directly or indirectly, use any AI System to perform
       AI-Assisted Reproduction of this Software. This prohibition applies
       regardless of whether the AI System:

         (a) Produces output that is textually identical to the Software;
         (b) Produces output that is functionally equivalent but textually
             distinct from the Software;
         (c) Operates on an intermediate artifact (such as a summary, analysis
             document, architecture diagram, or pseudocode representation)
             derived from the Software rather than on the Software directly;
         (d) Is operated by a human who subsequently edits or curates the
             AI-generated output before distribution.

  7.2  PROHIBITION ON MULTI-STAGE AI CLONING PIPELINES

       The prohibition in § 7.1 expressly extends to multi-stage workflows,
       including but not limited to:

         (a) "Analyze-then-Rebuild" pipelines, in which one agent or AI System
             reads and analyzes the Software (producing a report, summary,
             specification, or blueprint), and a second agent or AI System uses
             that artifact as the basis for generating a new codebase;

         (b) "Summarize-then-Generate" pipelines, in which the Software's
             architecture, logic, or design decisions are distilled into any
             intermediate format and subsequently used as a generation prompt
             or specification for a new system;

         (c) Automated fork-and-rewrite systems that ingest the Software via
             repository scraping, API access, or any other means and produce
             a restructured or paraphrased version of the codebase.

  7.3  PROHIBITION ON DERIVATIVE STRUCTURAL CLONING

       You may not create or distribute a project that constitutes Structural
       Cloning of this Software, even if no source code from this project was
       directly incorporated. Structural Cloning includes, but is not limited
       to:

         (a) Replicating the module hierarchy, component responsibility
             boundaries, or inter-module communication patterns of the Software
             in a new codebase without substantive independent design work;

         (b) Implementing a system whose behavioral interface, API surface,
             or configuration schema is designed to be a drop-in replacement
             for this Software without attribution and compliance with this
             License;

         (c) Recreating novel or non-obvious algorithmic solutions, data
             pipeline architectures, or heuristics that are original to this
             Software in a manner not independently derived.

  7.4  PERMITTED AI-ASSISTED ACTIVITIES

       Notwithstanding the foregoing, the following uses of AI Systems in
       connection with the Software are permitted:

         (a) Using AI Systems to assist in writing contributions to this
             Software that are submitted back to the official project under
             this License;

         (b) Using AI Systems for personal code comprehension, debugging
             assistance, or understanding the Software for the purpose of
             lawful use;

         (c) Using AI Systems to generate test cases, documentation
             improvements, or accessibility enhancements that are contributed
             back to the project;

         (d) Academic or research analysis of the Software, provided no
             resulting artifact is used as the basis for a Structural Clone
             or AI-Assisted Reproduction.

  7.5  TRAINING DATA RESTRICTION

       You may not use the Software, or any substantial portion thereof, as
       training data, fine-tuning data, reinforcement learning feedback,
       retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) context, or any other machine
       learning input for the purpose of enabling an AI System to generate
       code that replicates the Software's functionality, architecture, or
       design without compliance with this License.

  7.6  RESPONSIBILITY FOR AGENT-MEDIATED VIOLATIONS

       If an AI System acting under your direction, on your behalf, or using
       resources or credentials under your control commits an act prohibited
       under this section, you are deemed the responsible party for that
       violation and your license rights are subject to termination under § 10.

