§ 10. LICENSE TERMINATION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  10.1 Your rights under this License terminate automatically and without
       notice upon any material breach of its terms, including:

         (a) Failure to include required attributions (§ 2);
         (b) Failure to disclose Alpha status in redistributions (§ 3);
         (c) Failure to document modifications (§ 4);
         (d) Use of prohibited names or trademarks (§§ 5, 8);
         (e) Failure to provide source for binary distributions (§ 6);
         (f) Engaging in AI-Assisted Reproduction or Structural Cloning (§ 7);
         (g) Use of the Software as AI training data in violation of § 7.5;
         (h) Any breach of the base GPL v3.0 terms.

  10.2 Rights terminated under this section may only be reinstated by explicit
       written consent of the NEURO Project maintainers, or as provided by
       the cure provisions of GPL v3.0 § 8 for GPL-only violations.

  10.3 Termination of your rights does not affect the rights of parties who
       have received copies or Derivative Works from you in compliance with
       this License prior to the termination event.

